subject: [CI] Install dependencies for docs target

commit_message:
[CI] Install dependencies for docs target

When tox 'docs' target is called, first it installs the dependencies
(listed in 'deps') in 'installdeps' phase, then it installs murano
(with its requirements) in 'develop-inst' phase. In the latter case
'deps' is not used so that the constraints defined in 'deps' are not
used. This could lead to failures on stable branches when new packages
are released that break the build. To avoid this, the simplest solution
is to pre-install requirements, i.e. add requirements.txt to 'docs' tox
target.

Change-Id: I1d80bfc5f9c3fecc8551ffc8592e39f76b671485

"}, {'number': 9, 'created': '2016-08-17 09:36:15.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/murano/commit/97bb80d2a8b7dbf2b5fc82707eb48722a2d507f0', 'message': "Aspects event hooking

The first part of policy implementation is the mechanism to invoke
appropriate aspect methods on events in engine. Such events are
loading objects to the object store and loading packages.

Now it is possible:
* to write custom aspect code in the form of library package;
* to define the aspect rules in json-format and place it to the file
murano/common/aspects.py;
* aspects are notified of the objects load event and packages load
event;
* aspects can modify the values of object's properties.

The example policy enforces usage of some maximum instance flavor
and demonstrates hooking to the package load event.

Change-Id: Ic7c23af983392e8faf3055ee49dcf9581d516bbd
Partially-implements: bp application-policies

Commit includes:
* New package type Aspect which will have extended MuranoPL
  reflection capabilities. At this stage methods inside this type
  of packages have the ability to modify properties of any object
* New classes io.murano.policy.Aspect and io.murano.policy.Notifier
* Every aspect instance on its init subscribe to notifications of
  different events. For now it is only object initialization event.
  To subscribe, it passes itself, name of handler method and name
  of method to check some condition against the processed object
  to notifier's subscribe() method
* Example policy package that inforces usage of some maximum
  instance flavor with test-runner tests

So now it is possible:
* to write custom aspect code in the form of library package
* to define the aspect rules in json-format and place it to the file
  murano/common/aspects.py (until db tables and api are implemented)
* aspects are notified of the objects initializing event
* aspects can modify the values of object's properties

Change-Id: Ic7c23af983392e8faf3055ee49dcf9581d516bbd
Partially-implements: bp application-policies

commit_message:
Initial commit for application policy

Commit includes:
* New package type Aspect which will have extended MuranoPL
  reflection capabilities. At this stage methods inside this type
  of packages have the ability to modify properties of any object
* New classes io.murano.policy.Aspect and io.murano.policy.Notifier
* Every aspect instance can subscribe to notifications of
  different events. For now it is only object initialization event.
  To subscribe, it passes itself, name of handler method and name
  of method to check some condition against the processed object
  to notifier's subscribe() method
* Example policy package that inforces usage of some maximum
  instance flavor with test-runner based tests

So now it is possible:
* to write custom aspect code in the form of library package
* to define the aspect rules in json-format and place it to the file
  murano/common/aspects.py (until db tables and api are implemented)
* aspects are notified of the objects initializing event
* aspects can modify the values of object's properties

Change-Id: Ic7c23af983392e8faf3055ee49dcf9581d516bbd
Partially-implements: bp application-policies

commit_message:
Extended MuranoPL reflection and package load event

1. Methods inside Aspect packages provided with extended
   reflection capabilities:
     * changing type property default value
     * changing type property contract
     * changing method argument default value
     * changing method argument contract
2. Aspects are able to subscribe to package load event
3. DefaultSetter and ContractSetter example policies are added

Change-Id: I141b1f80b2b1e8aaf97d167734fefeeecdd72fed
Partially-implements: bp application-policies

commit_message:
Add RecordSet resource and zone list

This commit introduces a new io.murano.resources.RecordSet resource
type. When coupled with a commit to murano-dashboard, it allows
users to be able to select an available zone from a UI list and
have it passed to this RecordSet resource for provising a Designate
DNS record.

commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: Iee7476ec26e02e389efab473b6e3362d78cec1e6

commit_message:
drop mock from lower-constraints

The mock third party library was needed for mock support in py2
runtimes. Since we now only support py36 and later, we don't need it
in lower-constraints.

These changes will help us to drop `mock` from openstack/requirements

Change-Id: I676add1724c6557e3b0108222a2c2babe022c98c

commit_message:
fix requirements python supported minimal version

Some recent rules have been added to openstack/requirements
concerning:
- oslo.utils
- oslo.i18n
- oslotest
- reno

According to your supported runtimes these changes define the python
version for these requirements to fix CI jobs.

Change-Id: Ida4aef0864aff90f637102069755f510515870bf

commit_message:
Add networks properties for OS::Nova::Server resource

Since nova api version 2.37,  `networks` entry is required for the server
creation[1]. Plus a heat change[2] in release Rocky removes old workaround.
Therefore instance creation through heat orchestraction template needs
`networks` property of OS::Nova::Server resource in template.

While murano core library not passing this property to heat template makes
it fail to work with Rocky release heat.

The patch passes in `Auto` value to networks object for Instance class.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/nova/latest/reference/api-microversion-history.html#id34
[2] https://github.com/openstack/heat/commit/3c06347a93343850409a243b3c7e1f11eeb4db3f

Closes-Bug: #1817538

Change-Id: Idef60e2c13e1d4f3ea802504076110ea447d193d

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so in
controller-install-*.rst "-u root -p" is useless.

Change-Id: Iec2674440319f463ac892c2f2a845f6a3572b13f
Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
env.py is going around oslo_db

This fixes the issue of alembic going around oslo_db
facade. Now all oslo_db options are processed and passed
to the engine.

Change-Id: I78f6da9112eeade31d5502f73f01b4158a3bf714

commit_message:
[WIP] Added Tempest negative tests for sessions

Added negative tests for the scenarios:
    * get session without session id
    * delete session without session id
    * deploy two sessions in the same environment
    * delete a session that is in deploying state
    * delete the same session twice

Change-Id: I4da7dac0218912b7aa1cf96edbbc13bc58562bf8

commit_message:
[Test-Runner] Added a 'save' method to TestFixture

Added a 'save' method to TestFixture class, so test-runner-based tests
may serialize MuranoPL-objects into JSON representation. The same
method may optionally run an orphan-cleanup routine to execute
resource deallocation for the objects which are present in object
store but are not part of the object tree passed to the function.

Change-Id: I51c017eb2582e43929a9fa7f51bab4e06b83f4e5
Closes-bug: #1597747

commit_message:
Fix toggle action of packages

In package page, there are two bugs:
1. toggle active and toggle public button text won't change.
2. toast only shows "Toggled Public" or "Toggled Active" even you toggle packages to private or inactive.

Change-Id: I5e984a408f3099f715f51af0483732863967df1f

When creating a new instance, generate its name based on
tenant name, application name and a region, therefore not using
a complicated composite structure used in Murano (murano+hashed),
and just UI generated name is displayed.

Also, the new schema takes into account names of the already
created instances to avoid duplication. For now, the 'hostname'
field for applications are still readonly, that would be changed
as validation is implemented.

commit_message:
Modify instance naming schema

When creating a new instance, generate its name based on
tenant name, application name and a region, therefore not using
a complicated composite structure used in Murano (murano+hashed),
and just UI generated name is displayed.

Also, the new schema takes into account names of the already
created instances to avoid duplication. For now, the 'hostname'
field for applications are still readonly, that would be changed
as validation is implemented.

Co-Authored-By: Artem Tiumentcev <darland.maik@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Roman Bogorodskiy <rbogorodskiy@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: I7bd0758cf4b04a01531c788ebedc06a5c98fe523
Signed-off-by: Leonid Bogdanov <lbogdanov@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Deprecated error method

$http's deprecated custom callback method: .error() has been
removed in AngularJS 1.6. Use the standard .catch() promise
method instead.

Change-Id: I1aba520be66b91239785214f91c6e0a2ee984e55

commit_message:
Capabilities for user to manage packages categories

From user's perspective, this patch adds a button "Manage categories" in
"Packages" screen. If some packages are selected and the button
is clicked, a screen is opened in which a user can assign or
unassign categories from packages or leave them in an indeterminate
state and then update the selected packages.

Depends-On: I98116fce362af5eb4c64941f4c442dd81120e762
Implements: blueprint assign-category-button
Change-Id: I13f902f130446fd94d9e2b12a91df53a35314fab

commit_message:
Do not specify SESSION_ENGINE in murano-dashboard

Base openstack_dashboard/settings.py already sets to 'cache' backend
and it works just fine. Setting session engine to 'db' causes unwanted
complications and gives us no additional benefits.

Change-Id: I595a85471f344ea8a2b05a4f4ff00b9bdca865b5

commit_message:
Missing openstackId key when instances are not deployed.

This fix going to avoid a error 500 when the Instance is on the
Following states:
Deploying , Ready for Deploy or Deploy Failed.

Also fix bug that Stack names are not displayed on overview tab.

Change-Id: I3b1312db9e3ba94024a1c7fa64614cddfb6c6488
Closes-Bug: #1655769
Closes-Bug: #1661727

commit_message:
Use py3 as the default runtime for tox

Moving on py3 as the default runtime for tox to avoid to update this at each new cycle.

Wallaby support officially the following runtimes [1]:
- Python 3.8

During Victoria Python 3.7 was used as the default runtime [2] however this version isn't longer officially supported.

Change-Id: I097940e62fe023a2c67abcf666dfe8240a3b92be

commit_message:
Include private flavors when listing flavors

Previously private flavor IDs would resolve to 'unknown' due
to the client only asking for public flavors.

Change-Id: I0c19a2f76112cc9e915a79bac73136149a262f7f
Closes-bug: #1672592

commit_message:
Add project parameter to filters resource with admin role

Currently, an user admin can list all profiles, clusters,.. and I
can using name, limit, marker when list. But, when I have so many
clusters, profiles, ... I can't list them only in a project.

So, I hope this patch can resolve above problem.

Change-Id: I76bf03478938b2b42996898a9538aa40cf2643ac

commit_message:
Add support a user admin can do everything

A user with role admin can delete, update cluster, policy, ...
and attach, detach a policy to a cluster and see policy biding
in a cluster

Change-Id: Id014484697ab932ea01c47f8054055f3c626be79

subject: Support os-brick specific lock_path
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2022-07-11 11:21:21.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/2a76b5d967ab996c5041a4464f2232e115d34c02', 'message': "Support os-brick specific lock_path

As a new feature, os-brick now supports setting the location of file
locks in a different location from the locks of the service.

The functionality is intended for HCI deployments and hosts that are
running Cinder and Glance using Cinder backend.  In those scenarios the
service can use a service specific location for its file locks while
only sharing the location of os-brick with the other services.

To leverage this functionality the new os-brick code is needed and
method ``os_brick.setup`` needs to be called once the service
configuration options have been loaded.

The default value of the os-brick ``lock_path`` is the one set in
``oslo_concurrency``.

This patch adds support for this new feature in a backward compatible
way so code works even if using an os-brick version that doesn't have
this feature.  That is the case for many CI jobs that install os-brick
from PyPi instead of the code present in master.

The patch also ensures that ``tox -egenconfig`` includes the os-brick
configuration options when generating the sample config.

Change-Id: I1b81eb65bd145869e8cf6f3aabc6ade58f832a19
"}, {'number': 2, 'created': '2022-08-24 09:04:36.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/79c8d16e59c20b0d711ac965de14ba1696c874db', 'message': "Support os-brick specific lock_path

As a new feature, os-brick now supports setting the location of file
locks in a different location from the locks of the service.

The functionality is intended for HCI deployments and hosts that are
running Cinder and Glance using Cinder backend.  In those scenarios the
service can use a service specific location for its file locks while
only sharing the location of os-brick with the other services.

To leverage this functionality the new os-brick code is needed and
method ``os_brick.setup`` needs to be called once the service
configuration options have been loaded.

The default value of the os-brick ``lock_path`` is the one set in
``oslo_concurrency``.

This patch adds support for this new feature in a backward compatible
way so code works even if using an os-brick version that doesn't have
this feature.  That is the case for many CI jobs that install os-brick
from PyPi instead of the code present in master.  This requires an
os-brick version bump in the requirements.

The patch also ensures that ``tox -egenconfig`` includes the os-brick
configuration options when generating the sample config.

Change-Id: I1b81eb65bd145869e8cf6f3aabc6ade58f832a19
"}, {'number': 3, 'created': '2022-08-24 09:08:39.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/26c6515c511f46ae36f6bf4e56976ef4640e1c45', 'message': 'Support os-brick specific lock_path

commit_message:
Support os-brick specific lock_path

As a new feature, os-brick now supports setting the location of file
locks in a different location from the locks of the service.

The functionality is intended for HCI deployments and hosts that are
running Cinder and Glance using Cinder backend.  In those scenarios the
service can use a service specific location for its file locks while
only sharing the location of os-brick with the other services.

To leverage this functionality the new os-brick code is needed and
method ``os_brick.setup`` needs to be called once the service
configuration options have been loaded.

The default value of the os-brick ``lock_path`` is the one set in
``oslo_concurrency``.

This patch adds support for this new feature in a non backward
compatible way, so it requires an os-brick version bump in the
requirements.

The patch also ensures that ``tox -egenconfig`` includes the os-brick
configuration options when generating the sample config.

Change-Id: I1b81eb65bd145869e8cf6f3aabc6ade58f832a19

commit_message:
[WIP] add iniital health check to compute agent

This change add the first use of the healthcheck
decorator to a subset of compute manager perodic tasks.

The decoraotr will report the check as passed if the periodic
complete without raising an error or failed otherwise.

assuming nova was deployed with devstack the compute agent
will be configured to expose the healthcheck endpoint on port
42429 and the data can be queried with curl as follows

(.venv) sean@devstack-healthchecks:~/repos/nova$ curl http://127.0.0.1:42429/health | jq
  % Total    % Received % Xferd  Average Speed   Time    Time     Time  Current
                                 Dload  Upload   Total   Spent    Left  Speed
100   865  100   865    0     0   580k      0 --:--:-- --:--:-- --:--:--  844k
{
  "status": "pass",
  "version": "1.0",
  "serviceId": "04ce64cc-850f-4b54-bafd-e90ad1f113eb",
  "description": "compute",
  "notes": {
    "host": "devstack-healthchecks"
  },
  "checks": {
    "heal_instance_info_cache": {
      "name": "heal_instance_info_cache",
      "status": "pass",
      "time": "2024-01-26T18:40:50.462428",
      "output": null
    },
    "instance_usage_audit": {
      "name": "instance_usage_audit",
      "status": "pass",
      "time": "2024-01-26T18:40:49.443749",
      "output": null
    },
    "update_available_resource": {
      "name": "update_available_resource",
      "status": "pass",
      "time": "2024-01-26T18:40:50.788103",
      "output": null
    },
    "sync_scheduler_instance_info": {
      "name": "sync_scheduler_instance_info",

    },

      "name": "pending deleted instances",
      "status": "pass",
      "time": "2024-01-26T18:40:43.463920",

  }
}

commit_message:
Retire ec2-api project

ec2-api project is in inactive list since 2024.1
- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/emerging-technology-and-inactive-projects.html#current-inactive-projects

and there is no leader in 2024.2 cycle
- https://etherpad.opendev.org/p/2024.2-leaderless

notification:
- https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/3B43DDZRNL7WZRBLJURIN723JNYNFNQX/
Seeing project inactivities, open critical bug, and no maintainers
for this project, this commit propose to retire this project.

Retire Senlin project

- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/emerging-technology-and-inactive-projects.html#current-inactive-projects

and there is no leader in 2024.2 cycle.

notification:
- https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/RYKD442DFHJ7CPLU5QKDTZQAAPNPFADP/

Seeing project inactivities and no maintainers for this project,

commit_message:
Retire Sahara project

Sahara project is in inactive list since 2024.1
- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/emerging-technology-and-inactive-projects.html#current-inactive-projects

and there is no leader in 2024.2 cycle (TC appointed the PTL
for this project in 4 cycles out of last 5 cycles).
- https://etherpad.opendev.org/p/2024.2-leaderless

notification:
- https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/24M3WQXDE2DYN3GWDFHY52FNGNIXN4N3/

Seeing project inactivities, open critical bug, and no maintainers
for this project, this commit propose to retire this project.

commit_message:
add healthcheck tracker to nova context

This change adds the healthcheck tracker to the nova
context object by extedning the context module with a
module global _HEALTH_TRACKER and register_healthcheck_tracker
function. The RequestContext __init__ method is extended
with a health_tracker kwarg and the get_context and get_admin_context
functions are modifyied to pass _HEALTH_TRACKER.

These change allow the health tracker to be accessed from
any function that is passed the context object enabling fine grained
health checks to be added in future patches.

Implements: blueprint per-process-healthchecks
Change-Id: I2675794fbb37735189bf4c966508bb3771d1c2f5

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2019-08-12 20:15:08.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/devstack/commit/e21ece4dac62e48d1db765df4ac6d298e892a030', 'message': 'WIP: Use OSCaaS to speed up devstack runs

OpenStackClient has a significant amount of startup overhead, which
adds a non-trivial amount of time to each devstack run because it makes
a lot of OSC calls. This change uses the OSC service from [0] to run
a persistent process that handles openstack calls. This removes most
of the startup overhead and in my local testing removes about three
minutes per devstack run.

'}, {'number': 17, 'created': '2019-08-15 18:15:48.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/devstack/commit/28e3c80e0eb2abf310c492cb114404c91df33ba1', 'message': 'Use OSCaaS to speed up devstack runs

OpenStackClient has a significant amount of startup overhead, which
adds a non-trivial amount of time to each devstack run because it makes
a lot of OSC calls. This change uses the OSC service from [0] to run
a persistent process that handles openstack calls. This removes most
of the startup overhead and in my local testing removes about three
minutes per devstack run.

Currently this is implemented as an opt-in feature. There are likely a
lot of edge cases in projects that use a devstack plugin so turning it
on universally is going to require boiling the ocean. I think getting
this in and enabled for some of the major projects should give use a lot
of the benefit without the enormous effort of making it 100% compatible
across all of OpenStack.

Another thing to note is that the openstack-server doesn't seem to be
able to properly handle image upload commands, so I've stored off a
copy of the original path variable and use that when devstack makes
"openstack image create" calls. It works, but it feels a little hacky
to me so I'm open to other solutions. It does have the advantage of
providing a standard way to use the original OSC when necessary.

Since the devstack job definitions are used as the base job for many
other jobs, the ansible var is set in the check and gate sections
instead of the job definition itself so they only apply to the jobs
running in devstack itself.

Change-Id: I28e6159944746abe2d320369249b87f1c4b9e24e

commit_message:
Use OSCaaS to speed up devstack runs

OpenStackClient has a significant amount of startup overhead, which
adds a non-trivial amount of time to each devstack run because it makes
a lot of OSC calls. This change uses the OSC service from [0] to run
a persistent process that handles openstack calls. This removes most
of the startup overhead and in my local testing removes about three
minutes per devstack run.

Currently this is implemented as an opt-in feature. There are likely a
lot of edge cases in projects that use a devstack plugin so turning it
on universally is going to require boiling the ocean. I think getting
this in and enabled for some of the major projects should give us a lot
of the benefit without the enormous effort of making it 100% compatible
across all of OpenStack.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/nova/+/918689
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/ironic/+/918690
Change-Id: I28e6159944746abe2d320369249b87f1c4b9e24e

commit_message:
add healthcheck manager to manager base

This change adds the heathcheck manager to to
the service instances via the pre_start_hook

It also stubs out the healthcheck manager from
all tests that are not explictly testing it.

The healthcheck manager is initalized with the
service_ref.uuid, To enable this we also need to
set a uuid in the defualt fake service created
in the compute manager BaseTestCase.

Implements: blueprint per-process-healthchecks
Change-Id: I2d351743ec29beb1af41e8e31485c3287de08f1e

subject: add initial healthcheck support
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2022-01-17 21:38:12.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/0ff26c5aaef5f979c4398f7be7c69d96ba7279dd', 'message': '[WIP] add initial healthcheck support

This change add the healthcheck module and config options.

Currently these are not used and they will be enabled in a
later patch in the series.

you can test the healthcheck module locally by simply
importing the module and constucting the endpoint.
e.g.

from nova.healtcheck import manager as hm
hm.CONF.healthcheck.uri = 'tcp://0.0.0.0:42424'
manager = hm.HealthcheckManager()
manager.sleep(10)

the manager.sleep is needed to cause the interactive
python shell to yield to the eventlet eventloop.
then in another terminal you can use curl or any other client
e.g.
curl -v http://127.0.0.1:42424/health

*   Trying 127.0.0.1:42424...
* Connected to 127.0.0.1 (127.0.0.1) port 42424 (#0)
> GET /health HTTP/1.1
> Host: 127.0.0.1:42424
> User-Agent: curl/7.79.1
> Accept: */*
>
* Mark bundle as not supporting multiuse
< HTTP/1.1 200 OK
< Content-Type: application/health+json
< Cache-Control: max-age=300
< Content-Length: 36
< Date: Mon, 17 Jan 2022 19:36:19 GMT
<
* Connection #0 to host 127.0.0.1 left intact
{"status": "pass", "version": "1.0"}

Change-Id: I181799a4c8608422abdf4e3b49e53e715cbfb350

commit_message:
add initial healthcheck support

This change adds the healthcheck module and config options.

Currently these are not used and they will be enabled in a
later patch in the series.

You can test the healthcheck module locally by simply
importing the module and constructing the endpoint.
e.g.

from nova.healthcheck import manager as hm
hm.CONF.healthcheck.uri = 'tcp://0.0.0.0:42424'
manager = hm.HealthcheckManager('1', 'nova-api')
manager.sleep(10)

The manager.sleep is only needed in interactive
python shell to yield to the eventlet eventloop.
Once the manager is created in another terminal
you can use curl or any other client to test the endpoint
e.g.
curl -v http://127.0.0.1:42424/health

*   Trying 127.0.0.1:42424...
* Connected to 127.0.0.1 (127.0.0.1) port 42424 (#0)
> GET /health HTTP/1.1
> Host: 127.0.0.1:42424
> User-Agent: curl/7.79.1
> Accept: */*
>
* Mark bundle as not supporting multiuse
< HTTP/1.1 200 OK
< Content-Type: application/health+json
< Cache-Control: max-age=300
< Content-Length: 36
< Date: Mon, 17 Jan 2022 19:36:19 GMT
<
* Connection #0 to host 127.0.0.1 left intact
{"status": "pass", "version": "1.0"}

Implements: blueprint per-process-healthchecks
Change-Id: I181799a4c8608422abdf4e3b49e53e715cbfb350

commit_message:
Translate '\'-delimited paths on Windows to be '/'-delimited

This allows Windows clients to more easily upload "standard" object
names that will interact well with features like staticweb.

Closes-Bug: #1511813
Co-Authored-By: Tim Burke <tim.burke@gmail.com>
Change-Id: Iee5467e148d7f67134f8277148e300b340750103

commit_message:
Escape special characters in password for DB connection

The passwords with special characters need to be URL encoded to be
parsed correctly

commit_message:
Use Cinder's os-extend_volume_completion volume action.

When Nova receives a volume-extended external server event and the
status of the extended volume is 'extending', it will now notify Cinder
of success or failure when handling the event by using the new
os-extend_volume_completion volume action.

This change incidentally also fixes an issue where nova-compute would
create an instance action entry indicating success despite encountering
errors when extended the volume.

Closes-Bug: #1843008

Implements: bp/assisted-volume-extend
Change-Id: Ifaca903a333b0b39ae87e6dc152b8fb2ec849989

commit_message:
Fix cinder deployment script

Recently we introduced test jobs that consume
charts from either local or public Helm repos.
All the deployment scripts must use variables
OSH_HELM_REPO or OSH_INFRA_HELM_REPO
which by default point to local directories
but these new jobs set them to use HTTP repos.

Change-Id: I2e17790385c2bdc0b79607c240a47639c61365c0

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2024-05-14 18:12:57.000000000', 'files': ['devstack/lib/crio'], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/devstack-plugin-container/commit/e49c0a211ed183c1b167b83846213420cff46c76', 'message': "Change repositories for cri-o.

Last year cri-o project has followed kubernetes and move its\xa0builds to
new repository[1]. Starting from version 1.28 all the builds will be
available only from the new location. The old one still preserves older
builds, but it's difficult to make them work effortlessly, especially
for Centos based devstack deployments.

This patch changes location for installed packages for cri-o for Ubuntu
based deployments only, and rely on the semver version string in
CRIO_VERSION variable, instead of path fragment like we have it

commit_message:
Change repositories for cri-o.

Last year cri-o project has followed kubernetes and move itsbuilds to
new repository[1]. Starting from version 1.28 all the builds will be
available only from the new location. The old one still preserves older
builds, but it's difficult to make them work effortlessly, especially
for Centos based devstack deployments.

This patch changes location for installed packages for cri-o for Ubuntu
based deployments only, and rely on the semver version string in
CRIO_VERSION variable, instead of path fragment like we have it
currently.

[1] https://kubernetes.io/blog/2023/10/10/cri-o-community-package-infrastructure/

Change-Id: I8b6022900cd68851c43c7587078dd5a24e1f7116
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/devstack-plugin-container refs/changes/10/919610/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD

Where the order of commands are: Usage: swift formpost [--digest ] [--redirect ] [--max-file-count ] Generate Form Signature positional arguments: The amount of time the form post will be valid. The time can be specified in three ways: an integer representing the time in seconds; a number with a 's', 'm', 'h', or 'd' suffix to specify the time in seconds, minutes, hours, or days; or an ISO 8601 timestamp in a specific format. If --absolute is passed and time is an integer, the seconds are intepreted as the Unix timestamp when the temporary URL will expire. commit_message:
Add formpost subcommand to generate signature A couple of years ago[0] we moved the tempurl signature generation from a tool inside swift to a sub command in the client. This made a lot of sense. This patch does the same thing for formpost. It adds a new `formpost` sub command to the swiftclient shell. And a generate formpost signature helper method to utils, so now we can: swift formpost 500 5 "/v1/a/c" "some_key" --redirect 'http://gohere.example' --digest sha256 --max-file-count 1 500, 5, /v1/a/c, some_key Expires: 1709089853 Signature: 333de753c27f4d0d81d6bfa35af19da803d2b1f9ea90219973db846a2fe3e1d7 Sample form: NOTE: the
tag's "action" attribute does not obtain the Swift cluster's hostname. You should manually add it before using the form.
Where the order of commands are: Usage: swift formpost [--digest ] [--redirect ] [--max-file-count ] Generate Form Signature positional arguments: The amount of time the form post will be valid. The time can be specified in three ways: an integer representing the time in seconds; a number with a 's', 'm', 'h', or 'd' suffix to specify the time in seconds, minutes, hours, or days; or an ISO 8601 timestamp in a specific format. If --absolute is passed and time is an integer, the seconds are intepreted as the Unix timestamp when the temporary URL will expire. The ISO 8601 timestamp can be specified in one of following formats: i) Complete date: YYYY-MM-DD (eg 1997-07-16) ii) Complete date plus hours, minutes and seconds: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss (eg 1997-07-16T19:20:30) iii) Complete date plus hours, minutes and seconds with UTC designator: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ (eg 1997-07-16T19:20:30Z) Please be aware that if you don't provide the UTC designator (i.e., Z) the timestamp is generated using your local timezone. If only a date is specified, the time part used will equal to 00:00:00. max_file_size The maximum file size per file uploaded. path The prefix to use for form uploaded objects. For example: /v1/account/container/object_prefix_ would ensure all form uploads have that path prepended to the browser-given file name. key The X-{Account|Container}-Meta-Temp-URL-Key for the account/container. optional arguments: --absolute Interpret the positional argument as a Unix timestamp rather than a number of seconds in the future. If an ISO 8601 timestamp is passed for , this argument is ignored. --redirect The URL to redirect the browser to after the uploads have completed. --digest {sha256,sha512,sha1}, -a {sha256,sha512,sha1} Select the hash digest to use. Default sha256. --max-file-count The maximum number of uploaded files allowed. Default: 1 The default algorithm/digest is sha256. Change-Id: Idd318c7bdddea60e8ede7e310b51a270e93f764f

commit_message:
Add TLS proxy for novncproxy

This improvement enables TLS encryption for the novncproxy service, even
when enable_haproxy is False. This change is beneficial for operators
who run deployments using an external Load Balancer with enable_haproxy
set to False, but still require TLS encryption for the novncproxy
service.

Signed-off-by: Robert Breker
Signed-off-by: Oliver Schmitz

Change-Id: Ibb33aaf200f460c83ddeb9d0656ccaa6a655f142

Change-Id: Ib1326852a5abe95811fe2aa2b6d03e7d4ca57959

Ply-Patch: Add-TLS-proxy-for-novncproxy.patch
Change-Id: Idd295a4d4ea265e33a42e4c86830ca9d968fb2be

A fun issue can occur where "metalsmith list" returns an error
indicating "Request requires an ID but none was found".

What is happening is metalsmith list is collecting data from
multiple locations, and it has identified continuty error where
a node is deployed with an instance_id field having been set,
but it expect and did not find an allocation record for that
node.

This is a fairly fatal error, or at least was since it does not
need to be.

The allocation can be backfilled for metalsmith not to error,
and the list operation will do that for the user instead of
returning a hard error. If a hard error is still encountered,
then and only then is the error returned.

Change-Id: I033a9925fe798f329b7bb9a629da0cd0f1202683

to return a list of instances which have been deployed
or are managed using metalsmith. The challenge is if someone
didn't create an allocation record, or if someone used the
metalsmith modules to do so when the node was in a maintenance
state, for example if BMC communication was not working.

The underlying challenge is this results in a lack of an allocation
record from being created. This can be manually corrected, and instead
of providing a vague error, metalsmith now provides a detailed error
with the command to remedy the error state through manual creation of
the allocation record, which allows "metalsmith list" to work as
expected.

commit_message:
Error with clarity when a bad upgrade was encountered

Metalsmith is generally used as a frontend for baremetal
provisioning such that a user can ask for baremetal to be
deployed with a simplified command line. The challenge is
it artificially hydrates together data from several queries
to return a list of instances which have been deployed
or are managed using metalsmith. The challenge is if someone
didn't create an allocation record, or if someone used the
metalsmith modules to do so when the node was in a maintenance
state, for example if BMC communication was not working.

The underlying challenge is this results in a lack of an allocation
record from being created. This can be manually corrected, and instead
of providing a vague error, metalsmith now provides a detailed error
with the command to remedy the error state through manual creation of
the allocation record, which allows "metalsmith list" to work as
expected.

Change-Id: I033a9925fe798f329b7bb9a629da0cd0f1202683

commit_message:
Allow domain users to manage credentials

Credentials are associated with users so there is no reason we prevent
domain users from accessing the resources. In some services like heat
domain admin is used to generate keystone credentials and loosing
the scope check is required to continue supporting such use case.

Closes-Bug: #2062045
Change-Id: I140b302d879ce1cc1f8d8de9e666cc74278a977f

commit_message:
Allow ml2 drivers to start their own RPC listeners

To allow MechanismDrivers to start their own RPC listeners (e.g. for
communication with custom agents) the MechanismManager will now call
start_rpc_listeners() of each driver. This is done as part of
Ml2Plugin.start_rpc_listeners(). It is added as an alternative to create
the backends in initialize(), as in cases where a driver is split up
into the API and RPC part we want to make sure these backends are only
started in the RPC part of neutron.

This patch depends on MechanismDrivers.start_rpc_listeners() in
neutron-lib[0].

[0] https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/neutron-lib/+/919589

Change-Id: I31e253180f474abf6d266d23c50f9dc89f17f687
Closes-Bug: #2065198

commit_message:
Add start_rpc_listeners() to MechanismDriver

This method will allow MechanismDrivers to start their own RPC
listeners, if they require some, e.g. for communication between the
driver and a custom agent. It is added as an alternative to create the
backends in initialize(), as in cases where a driver is split up into
the API and RPC part we want to make sure these backends are only
started in the RPC part of neutron.

start_rpc_listeners() is modeled after
NeutronPluginBaseV2.start_rpc_listeners() and will be called as part of
start_rpc_listeners() of the Ml2Plugin.

Change-Id: I5c50305bd3273318a1cdf393bbda9d33bdd91e4d
Partial-Bug: #2065198

commit_message:
Bundle the os-brick library in the Glance image

Glance uses the os-brick library to attach and detach Cinder volumes
in case the Cinder volume backend uses iSCSI/FC/NVMeoF as the underlying
storage protocol.

One such case is when using volume-backend images with Cinder volume
backends that support volume cloning.

Change-Id: I2ba690d78c560bee6e9e4e562c9dbe4f2ce09318

commit_message:
Add qos_prefetch_count to variables

When rabbit_stream_fanout is set to true, rabbit_qos_prefetch_count
should be set to a positive value.

This also fixes defenition of transient_quorum_queue as if
rabbit_stream_fanout is enabled - transient_quorum_queue should be also
enabled. [1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/master/oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_rabbit.py#L726-L736

Change-Id: Ia10d3945717f07051680e72552e38f2e2d4ddf12

commit_message:
Improve terminology in project-config tree

There is no real reason we should be using some of the
terms we do, they're outdated, and we're behind other
open-source projects in this respect. Let's switch to
using more inclusive terms in all possible places.

Updated playbooks and related code accordingly.

setup: Remove pbr's wsgi_scripts

This is technical dead end and not something we're going to be able to
support long-term in pbr. We need to push users away from this.

Change-Id: Ib7ea7fa00f8a4cc97f20e01fbd0357f737a6c224
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>
Depends-on: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/devstack/+/919581

commit_message:
Ensure app/filter factory options exist

All middleware filters and apps enabled in pipeline should have
the corresponding factory option (use = ... ) but the lines may not
exist in case the config file does not exist or is generated in advance
incompletely.

Change-Id: I714fe28547ea8308d7e82b66687ea0f24f816cda

subject: [devstack] Upload images with --file instead of stdin
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2024-05-08 18:03:42.000000000', 'files': ['devstack/lib/ironic'], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/ironic/commit/a0f48b64259ebe6e6b0bdd25f2b1585527a0495a', 'message': "[devstack] Upload images with --file instead of stdin

This makes all the image upload commands in the devstack plugin use
--file instead of stdin redirection, and also uses an absolute path.
One of the commands was already doing it this way. By doing the upload
like this, it makes the devstack plugin usable with the OCaaS devstack
mode (for faster openstack client ops) since we can't pass the image
stream via stdin. Most people will be using --file for uploading
anyway, so this is probably more realistic anyway.

Change-Id: I8d97ed731133d02aed46a078c50769692ad7ba04
"}]
commit_message:
[devstack] Upload images with --file instead of stdin

This makes all the image upload commands in the devstack plugin use
--file instead of stdin redirection, and also uses an absolute path.
One of the commands was already doing it this way. By doing the upload
like this, it makes the devstack plugin usable with the OCaaS devstack
mode (for faster openstack client ops) since we can't pass the image
stream via stdin. Most people will be using --file for uploading
anyway, so this is probably more realistic anyway.

Change-Id: I8d97ed731133d02aed46a078c50769692ad7ba04

commit_message:
openvswitch: Stop using intermediate scripts

This will fix exit codes - details in bug.

Basically openvswitch treats TERM as something fatal (exits
with 143) and the only solution for graceful exit is using
ovs-appctl and sending exit command, just like ovs-ctl utility
does.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/kolla/+/905189

Partial-Bug: #2048130
Change-Id: I523018cb98944de60d7b95404deb7cebd641f33a

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible-plugins/+/914144
Change-Id: I061653c3976458c0161915b7273f1ee2c575df13

commit_message:
Fix upload with "parent-relative" file paths

This fix strips leading parent dir "short string" or "short hand" (../),
ensuring correct container and pseudo-folder/object creation and naming
when a "parent-relative" file path (../file_in_parent_dir) is passed for
upload.
(please see referenced bug for bug description)

Change-Id: I46c5d8764d5796dc33f87d70d588ce2f6fedf561
Closes-Bug: #1541018

commit_message:
Remove six library from requirements.txt

Six is unused in the code, and generally unused in all of
Openstack, so remove it.

Unfortunately this does not fix the py312 job.

commit_message:
When we failed to load pkcs12 cert print warning

Print actual error when we failed to load pkcs12 cert and
falling back to the default implemntation, as exception may
not be related to certificate or its format like an issue
with wrong methods during cryptography version mismatch

*** AttributeError: module 'OpenSSL.crypto' has no attribute 'load_pkcs12'

Related-Prod: PRODX-39931
Change-Id: I85c8a615c4f2e08e28939805ae0e9b2028dadaed
(cherry picked from commit 96846e7b66f50ed0af7ce99f547e7d2e9cb2cda6)

commit_message:
Fix DB deadlock in quotas

There's a potential deadlock when creating the first LB in a new
project. The query that creates an empty quota object for the project
may have triggered a deadlock in the DB, this deadlock should have been
handlded by an oslo_db.api.wrab_db_retry decorator but the decorated
function was incorrect called: the DB session must begin in the
decorated function and not in the caller.
If begin is called by the caller, in case of retry sqlalchemy will
complain that the session was not correctly restarted after a rollback.

Closes-Bug: #2038798
Change-Id: Iec1f8f8f61d77640d4a33d7ffb62925f7e860286
(cherry picked from commit 333f035ed2db77969e50b8762155d93057b2b328)

commit_message:
Fix rootwrap files idempotency

Task for ensuring rootwrap permissions adds execution bit to all files
in folders. Otherwise, rootwrap.d directory won't have it.

So using file module with recurse is not giving expected behaviour in any
scenario.
We just remove this task, since expected permissions must be set by prior
tasks.

Change-Id: I6853af8adc53d670ef1935dedebab75c1703a41c

commit_message:
Add parameters to cinder backend configuration

Add configuration parameters cinder_store_user_name,
cinder_store_password, cinder_store_project_name and
cinder_store_auth_address to cinder volume type backend configuration.
This avoids a glance_store bug that prevents glance-api from starting.

Closes-Bug: #2052726
Change-Id: I4b6ca32ed426f77a326711c2457046dbda594e77
(cherry picked from commit 07da644b2ba6a2371cf7ef5249e196f18a3b8823)

commit_message:
add healthcheck utils and constants

This change factors out the HealthcheckStatus enum
and cache contol constants into a seperate module

This change introduces a healthcheck utils module
which provide a healthcheck context manager and
healtcheck decorator which automaticaly record
the healthcheck status item based on if the wrapped
code exits normally or raises an expected error.

Change-Id: Id58a0978a34d7a208fd1caa4ff2b718fd926ca19

commit_message:
Fix health monitor information retrieval in API response

Closes bug: #2038367

Behavior: In the response body of the LB API when creating
a new load balancer, the information about the health
monitor is always null, even though it has been configured.

Reproduce: Using the Octavia API to create a new LB with
all components. You cannot see any information about the
health monitor that will be returned.

Proposed Fix: Modify the assignment to use
`data_model.health_monitor` instead of `pool.healthmonitor`.

Change-Id: Ia914ad89b6fdf3606c3d4bff0a4c425348c15e0c
(cherry picked from commit 7261730dffce4bd7cac4f3f0bfe1f97a43599e0b)

commit_message:
Fix incorrect masquerade rules in multivip LBs

The up scripts of the interface files were called only when the
interface moved from down to up, it means that they were not called
during the update of the configuration of an interface. So if during an
update, if an ipv6 subnet was plugged while the ipv4 subnet was already
there, the up script that sets the masquerade rules was not called.

It broke connectivity for either ipv4 or ipv6 between the client and the
members in UDP listeners in multivip load balancers.

Closes-Bug: #2037943

Change-Id: Iad78de1764bc3a3f699b5feef9e58999d2efe613
(cherry picked from commit 5c051a6ab6604c0cc38d59e1fdc0e6b199ed9932)

commit_message:
Remove SQLAlchemy tips jobs

The most recent SQLAlchemy and Alembic versions are now in
upper-constraints. As a result, this job has served its purpose and can
be removed. For more information, see [1].

[1] https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/RBHXHTO3GUOOXVSZXD4C2O3TKDOH2QSC/

Change-Id: I96ae5ba24a9e32994f4b7b111a8b56e56db33cbe
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>
Depends-on: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/requirements/+/879743

subject: Improve terminology in the requirements tree
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2024-04-30 19:18:00.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/requirements/commit/afc0b1aff0484336c3c3222940dafa08073bc6f8', 'message': "Improve terminology in the requirements tree

There is no real reason we should be using some of the
terms we do, they're outdated, and we're behind other

commit_message:
Improve terminology in the requirements tree

There is no real reason we should be using some of the
terms we do, they're outdated, and we're behind other
open-source projects in this respect. Let's switch to
using more inclusive terms in all possible places.

Change-Id: I90ac679c1745a31474c6f24ec7953624ad056d79

commit_message:
Fix neutron setting overrides

Since 2023.2, we deprecated some settings in the [neutron] section
('endpoint', 'endpoint_type' and 'ca_certificates_file'), they are
respectively replaced by 'endpoint_override', 'valid_interfaces' and
'cafile'. There's some code in Octavia that automatically sets the new
settings if the user still has the old settings (it is required because
keystoneauth uses the CONF objects to establish the sessions).
But some corner cases were not correctly addressed in that patch.

Now Octavia ensures that the override of the parameters is correctly
handled.

Conflicts:
	octavia/common/config.py

Change-Id: Ic37e9f699e32431ae1735ddc9642689967ddc696
Closes-Bug: 2051604
(cherry picked from commit 7bb6096eccc7966bd963a0529dc7b352246dfdbb)

commit_message:
libvirt: Cap with max_instances GPU types

We want to cap a maximum mdevs we can create.
If some type has enough capacity, then other GPUs won't be used and
existing ResourceProviders would be deleted.

Closes-Bug: #2041519
Change-Id: I069879a333152bb849c248b3dcb56357a11d0324
(cherry picked from commit 60851e44649e463bfda25d9dea84443467e4a30c)

commit_message:
ovn: don't log about rev number bumped when it was not bumped

Since Ib74fdab7a8927ef9cc24ef7810e9cf2c264941eb, we no longer bump
neutron resources' revision numbers when no actual changes are applied.
Still, we were logging a debug message for OVN revision number bump.

This patch skips the message in this scenario.

Reported-By: Yatin Karel <ykarel@redhat.com>

Related-Bug: #2065094
Change-Id: Ib9af5b02cfb8a5df3f36df4ddcc11b1f3e46c4eb

commit_message:
Add service policies defenition

In order to allow definition of policies per service, we need to add variables
to service roles, that will be passed to openstack.osa.mq_setup.

Currently this can be handled by leveraging group_vars and overriding `oslomsg_rpc_policies` as a whole, but it's not obvious and
can be non-trivial for some groups which are co-locating multiple services
or in case of metal deployments.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible/+/914188
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible-os_gnocchi/+/918036
Change-Id: Ib53e0822e5d7f52f1081a54c27c9f6bdcd8561d5

commit_message:
Cleanup duplicate DB sessions for quotas

Some functions in Octavia receive 2 DB session parameter, one is a
session in "autocommit" mode, the other without "autocommit" mode.

Now that the autocommit feature is removed from sqlalchemy, we can clean
up some leftovers of this migration, 2 session objects were passed to
these functions (and sometime the same object), only one is needed.

Related-Bug: #2038798
Change-Id: I070d27df8acc069836a8c7d4b0cf492c5b6a6168
(cherry picked from commit 2a1c4709a0f4a14510ef48358f4063034c28027a)

commit_message:
Drop Focal integration testing

There are projects which no longer support python3.8 in our integration
test. This means they cannot be installed on Ubuntu Focal any longer
without extra steps like checking out old eol tags. Rather than try and
keep up with this list (that will only grow over time) we drop the Focal
integration test and simply rely on unittesting for python3.8 and older.

This is in line with previous decisions made for python2.7 testing. It
isn't ideal, but should still provide sufficient coverage for the most
glaring incompatibilities we may try to introduce.

Change-Id: I7c80e93627597101cbed64a0efdc18140dbc854a

commit_message:
Fix zuul error about invalid regex

Fix zuul error:

All regular expressions must conform to RE2 syntax, but an
expression using the deprecated Perl-style syntax has been detected.
Adjust the configuration to conform to RE2 syntax.

The RE2 syntax error is: invalid perl operator: (?!

Change-Id: I03b4c63fe20db873825346be442dc6d5dfaaf4ec

commit_message:
Upload images with --file instead of stdin

This is more likely how people will actually upload their images, but
it also prevents the "osc as a service" feature from working because
stdin isn't proxied (of course). So just convert our uses of "image
create" to use --file instead of stdin.

Change-Id: I7205eb0100ba7406650ed609cf517cba2c8d30aa

commit_message:
Respect SSL settings in placement API

Make the placement API client respect the OPENSTACK_SSL_NO_VERIFY and
OPENSTACK_SSL_CACERT configuration options, so that it can work properly
in TLS-everywhere deployments.

Change-Id: Id0bb085bdf411eef240c3d50da56016c0a1d075c
(cherry picked from commit 14212342cf8f7eb987e50de112958af31063e02e)

commit_message:
Add stable/2024.1 jobs on master gate

As 2024.1 is released, we should add its job on master
gate to keep branchless tempest plugins compatible to stable branch.

Ref: Tempest plugins guide for stable branch testing:
- https://docs.openstack.org/tempest/latest/stable_branch_testing_policy.html

Change-Id: I01fb12fce6e5ac81c9112d9a7a834d97aea5eccc

'}, {'number': 4, 'created': '2021-06-28 14:49:00.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/cinder/commit/36ba8f98c50934c4a911da34c00a48f1be1e52f5', 'message': 'Query internal project/user id from Keystone

Cinder has provided cinder_internal_teant_project/user_id to define
its internal project and user, but these are not predictable thus
users always need to set up keystone and create an internal project
and user to define these parameters.

This change introduces the new internal_tenant section in cinder.conf
which accepts keystoneauth parameters. With these parameters, users
are now allowed to define internal project and user by names and cinder
automatically looks up ids from Keystone.
Note that this change also lets cinder to ensure that its internal
project and user actually exists in Keystone.

Closes-Bug: #1933052
Change-Id: Ibd62f3176c84e90e1fb3999d9d68681763aa0a5c

commit_message:
Query internal project/user id from Keystone

Cinder has provided cinder_internal_teant_project/user_id to define
its internal project and user, but these are not predictable thus
users always need to set up keystone and create an internal project
and user to define these parameters.

This change introduces the new internal_tenant section in cinder.conf
which accepts keystoneauth parameters. With these parameters, users
are now allowed to define internal project and user by names and cinder
automatically looks up ids from Keystone.

Note that this change also lets cinder to ensure that its internal
project and user actually exists in Keystone to detect any mis-
configurations.

DocImpact

Closes-Bug: #1933052
Change-Id: Ibd62f3176c84e90e1fb3999d9d68681763aa0a5c

commit_message:
Fix issues seen with latest netaddr library

There are a few unit tests failing with this error:

  TypeError: inet_pton() argument 2 must be str, not MagicMock

The reason is there is no default return value from the mocking
of the internal network.

Correctly mock "resolve_address" to be an IP address as
is done in other tests, making netaddr happy.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I5151097a53651db0ff054b6649326c8a03e56ddd

commit_message:
Use deb822 format for Apt repositories on Ubuntu and drop apt-key

Use the modern deb822 format [1] for Apt repositories on Ubuntu the
same way as in OpenStack Kolla projects, for example in Kayobe [2].
Also this change refactor usage of the deprecated [3] apt-key tool.

[1] https://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/jammy/en/man5/sources.list.5.html#deb822-style%20format
[2] I3f821937b0930a0ac9341178de7ae5123d82b957
[3] https://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/jammy/en/man8/apt-key.8.html#deprecation

Change-Id: Ic3dd0ce30a8436406a451276bbd94cb5f6f33f9d
Signed-off-by: Maksim Malchuk <maksim.malchuk@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Do not load api-paste.ini using oslo.config

We expect that the api-paste.ini file contains pipeline definitions for
paste, which are different from service options. Thus we should not
load this file using oslo.config.

Change-Id: Ic03c5f9295e95bd967ab8d305ed8340b6e69e235

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I10a5d4c14aca341bb4ba9272fc919ec050670c20

commit_message:
Improve terminology in project-team-guide tree

There is no real reason we should be using some of the
terms we do, they're outdated, and we're behind other
open-source projects in this respect. Let's switch to
using more inclusive terms in all possible places.

Updated docs accordingly.

Change-Id: If05f346cc8a0fbb23e9a2ceb0dbc5a392425b692

commit_message:
nova: Release 2023.2 Bobcat 28.1.0

Bumping MINOR version due to dropping added functionality (libvirt
patches: stop enabling evmcs and reenlightenment; for details about
why we needed this backport, please see the release notes & the
discussion in patch [1])

$ git log --oneline --no-merges 28.0.1..HEAD
1bbd44e16e Fix nova-manage image_property show unexpected keyword
c5a73e6c72 pwr mgmt: handle live migrations correctly
95bbb0432a Reproducer test for live migration with power management
2a0e63828b pwr mgmt: make API into a per-driver object
4bcf5adada Power on cores for isolated emulator threads
3dde97216c Reproducer for not powering on isolated emulator threads cores
62a35d2324 Add cpuset_reserved helper to instance NUMA topology
45a926156c Fix nova-metadata-api for ovn dhcp native networks
436e525a97 libvirt: stop enabling hyperv feature reenlightenment
0b7a59ad28 libvirt: Stop unconditionally enabling evmcs
0a55ec33e6 Fixes: bfv vm reboot ends up in an error state.
19a4402fc2 Updates glance fixture for create image
891d1773a2 cpu: make governors to be optional
25d0db782e Revert "[pwmgmt]ignore missin governor when cpu_state used"
4239d1fec2 Do not untrack resources of a server being unshelved
477ff2667d Reproduce bug #2025480 in a functional test
989ee44890 Allow live migrate paused instance when post copy is enabled
b81439e2a2 Remove outdated comment about allocation ratios
55ed5765fa Fix traits to cpu flags mapping
3c054dc6c5 [pwmgmt]ignore missin governor when cpu_state used
fb59ca63ec Fix URLs in status check results

[1] https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/nova/+/909082

Change-Id: I1c03e11dd2d8f91b008b88ccc089db79a281185d

commit_message:
Add fake ironic python agent (fake_ipa)

This implimentation help to test ironic scalability.

As the existing fake system driver simulate VMs this
fake_ipa simulate the IPA by:

- Running an API server with the needed real IPA endpoint.
- Send back fake inspection data when requested.
- lookup the node and save tokens.
- Heartbeating to ironic API with several threads looping over
  a queue of fake agents.
- Faking the sync/async commands needed by ironic to inspect,
  clean and provision a node.

Co-authored-by: Furkat Gofurov <furkat.gofurov@est.tech>
Co-authored-by: Huy Mai <huy.mai@est.tech>

Change-Id: Ideede495d4c093c6f9ea544b4ad9206070832dba
Signed-off-by: Mohammed Boukhalfa <mohammed.boukhalfa@est.tech>

commit_message:
Fix ignored [castellan] barbican_* options

This change fixes the following two parameters which were ignored, and
ensures these parameters are properly passed to the castellan library.

 - barbican_api_endpoint
 - barbican_api_version.

The default value of barbican_api_version is updated to keep
the previous default behavior.

Story: 2009739
Task: 44168
Change-Id: Id54e135631897d1e5345286ef2ffdf38e5f54d75

commit_message:
Fix racy DHSS=True share groups test

We recently addressed a bug in Manila where
share networks couldn't be deleted when they were
still associated with any share groups [1]. After this
fix, we had a couple of tests failing sporadically
because they weren't waiting for the deletion of
the share groups prior to attempting deletion
of the share network subnets.

Change-Id: I532ff3f0b2613340e0cb46c3b7e57a22cfa50c61
Related-Bug: #2004212
Closes-Bug: #2064673
Signed-off-by: Goutham Pacha Ravi <gouthampravi@gmail.com>

Remove support for amqp1 messaging driver

It was deprecated during the 2023.2 cycle[1], so can be removed now.

Also add validation about transport_url options to reject unsupported
drivers.

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I88e1fd869fa0e1e13184d17d5fa16364f87d14bd

commit_message:
Add service secret to libvirt when cinder enabled

The current code only adds the service secret to libvirt when Ceph has
been enabled in Nova, but it should also be enabled if it has only been
enabled in Cinder.

This patch changes devstack/plugin.sh to write the service secret to
libvirt whenever Nova or Cinder is using Ceph.

This would be the counterpart of the code we already have in
_undefine_virsh_secret where we are already checking if it's enabled in
either of the services to remove the secret.

Change-Id: I1067d52b7a435fcef7996eea6479d598be842dca
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/devstack-plugin-ceph refs/changes/74/885374/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD

commit_message:
[api-ref] fix resource lock api reference

"delete" was the only lock action supported when
we introduced the API; but we now support "show"
as well for the access rules resource.

Also fix an incorrect parameter in the PUT /resource-locks
method.

Change-Id: Ic5828f73fbe613d7c1f46933155dffe06c7f288b
Signed-off-by: Goutham Pacha Ravi <gouthampravi@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Remove the rest of ietadm

The IET target was removed in Zed, remove
the remaining config references to it.

Use of the "ietadm" target_helper would have
already caused initialization of the LVM driver
to fail, as the iet class is missing.

Change-Id: I257432b6e4947f7084763069ce067c7d3e31528e

Spliting healthmonitor test for each pool protocol

Split the healthmonitor traffic tests for different pool
LB protocols, in order to have a better granularity and not
just running over ROUND_ROBIN.

commit_message:
OSP 18.0 RFE

cinder backup needs to restore thin volumes (new volumes only)
This test will loop through the backends, create backup and restore
it to the default backup backend.
This way we will catch all scenario where the volume backend and
the restored backend are different.

Change-Id: I8a740413ed3fe35addaca6916265d326d90b3b33
Signed-off-by: ybenshim <ybenshim@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Allow domain users to manage credentials

Credentials are associated with users so there is no reason we prevent
domain users from accessing the resources. In some services like heat
domain admin is used to generate keystone credentials and loosing
the scope check is required to continue supporting such use case.

Closes-Bug: #2062045
Change-Id: I140b302d879ce1cc1f8d8de9e666cc74278a977f
(cherry picked from commit 5ead95ffcc597517feed53170e2d2f77cdd311a1)

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Change-Id: Id9bc7f2ba4a2e813657d65f2bb6be5089c1a5461

commit_message:
Fix Dell OS6 and Dell OS9 switch configuration

Previously the dellos6_config and dellos9_config modules accepted the
name of a template file as their 'src' parameter, or a string containing
the actual config. Now they only accept the config string. Kayobe passes
the name of a template file, resulting in a strange error from the
switch about an invalid command dellos6-config.j2 or dellos9-config.j2.

This change fixes the issue in the same way it was fixed for Dell OS10
switches, by using the template lookup plugin to evaluate the config
file template.

Change-Id: Ic14e2b75c785b4db03b5e659e5a2be2ee83eace3
Closes-Bug: #2061102
(cherry picked from commit 67f09241e07b3119bb17ed59df2b40aa3c9dced9)

commit_message:
redis: Generate tls certs timely for redis-sentinel

The same certs are used by not only redis but also redis-sentinel so
the certs should be generated at the appropriate timing for sentinel
installation/configuration.

from the external interface layer instead of the internal interface.

commit_message:
baremetal: Add 'details' parameter to various 'find' proxy methods

In change I13f32e6ca9be9ed4eb42398aace47e3c5205a81f, we introduced
support for a 'details' parameter to various proxy methods that
supported it. Unfortunately there was a bug in the baremetal proxy layer
changes, which were using a mixin to modify the 'Resource.list' class
method to allow listing detailed responses easily via the resource
layer. This necessitated a revert, change
Icc70bbdc06b5f32722a93775aee2da4d7b7ca4ae.

Take another go at this by reverting the revert and making the necessary
changes to the mixin and proxy layer to make things compatible. We also
fix a few bugs, where certain resources has the mixin applied, resulting
in them attempting to use legacy path-based mechanism to retrieve
detailed resources (GET /resource/detail) even though they didn't
support this.

Change-Id: I6acbcb4d9af35e68c04bb86e50c8844487bd7d6c
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>

commit_message:
initialize DPDK interfaces for OVN

This adds another INIT container to initialize DPDK interfaces for
OVN. I prefered this in the OVN charts but really didn't want
another place for all the DPDK values that already existed in the
Neturon chart. Essentially, just copied the OVS agent init
container manifest that does this for an OVS without OVN config.

Also changed the br-phys to br-ex bridge name because that is a
default in both the OVN and neutron charts to use.
Otherwise you'd have an orphaned br-ex doing nothing in the config.

Change-Id: I2426d7b959503f2fc6add7610c9f52fc71369ef2

commit_message:
Add stable/2024.1 job on gate and remove zed job

As 2024.1 is released, we should add its job on master
gate to keep branchless tempest plugins compatible to
stable branch.

At the same time, we're dropping the zed job
since the zed branch of openstack/manila has now
transitioned to "unmaintained". manila-tempest-plugin
may no longer support running against the zed branch.
Please use the "zed-last" tag instead [1]

Ref: Tempest plugins guide for stable branch testing:
- https://docs.openstack.org/tempest/latest/stable_branch_testing_policy.html

[1] https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/releases/+/918346
Change-Id: I0625576d14d9e084aa65beed5d0c988dcebd85dc
Signed-off-by: Goutham Pacha Ravi <gouthampravi@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Remove publish-openstack-octavia-amphora-image jobs

These jobs run only in master. The current definition is causing
the following warnings.

  All regular expressions must conform to RE2 syntax, but an
  expression using the deprecated Perl-style syntax has been detected.
  Adjust the configuration to conform to RE2 syntax.

  The RE2 syntax error is: invalid perl operator: (?!

Conflicts:
  zuul.d/jobs.yaml
  zuul.d/projects.yaml

Change-Id: I5c882abd9ed2f36ae6ef70279f98a157d9910fd8

commit_message:
Replaces qnap driver XML with defusedxml

Replaces qnap driver's use of Python's
Standard XML library methods with defusedxml's
methods instead.The defusedXML protects the app
from XML attacks.
Instructed bandit to skip the line 86 of api.py
of qnap driver. _create_unverified_context was
intentionally used by developer which bandit
wasn't happy about.

Change-Id: I171c90a281c7b62c2601131293f9f00a926641e2

commit_message:
CI: Remove grenade branch variables

This was always testing the upgrade with master, causing CI failures on
the stable/2024.1 branch.

Also remove USE_PYTHON3 which is always true in our supported branches.

Change-Id: I9ba2b02b7c5abd2b6a2114cd3b680ea0244484a4

commit_message:
Preserve actual production playbook in examples

Since Murano is moved to inactive state, we can not provide further
releases of the role either, which means that Sahara should be dropped
from the integrated repo.

With that it's worth to preserve actuall playbook that was used for
deployment as example playbook, in case somebody needs to use old
role/service version in their deployments.

Change-Id: Iffcf7e865591ef76f62053f3ec3d022a90cfb331

commit_message:
Remove unused images after upgrade

All images that were used by containers
previous to the upgrade and are no longer
used will be removed. Any images that
were already on the host wil be untouched.

Closes-Bug: #1632282
Change-Id: I400244d4c51ff574dc967206a7c19d97414afd35
Signed-off-by: Roman Krek <roman.krcek@tietoevry.com>

commit_message:
tests: Handle short stats read

Occasionally we'll see test failures like the following in CI:

  openstack.tests.unit.test_stats.TestStats.test_servers_error
  ------------------------------------------------------------

  Captured traceback:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Traceback (most recent call last):

    ...

    Exception: Key openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.500 not found in reported stats

  Captured statsd_content:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    [b'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.500:1.000000|ms\nopenstack.api.compute.'
     b'GET.servers.500:1|c\nopenstack.api.compute.GET.servers.attempted:1|c']

Looking at the captured log, it's obvious that we've had a short read.
I'm not sure why this is happening - perhaps resource contention or
threads stepping on each other's toes - but it causes random failures.
This is because when we parse the list we end up with a split line, e.g.

  [
    'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.500:1.000000|ms',
    'openstack.api.compute.',
    'GET.servers.500:1|c',
    'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.attempted:1|c',
  ]

instead of

  [
    'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.500:1.000000|ms',
    'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.500:1|c',
    'openstack.api.compute.GET.servers.attempted:1|c',
  ]

Work around the issue by concatenating to a byte string instead. This
means we'll only ever split on the newline character. It's a bit of a
hack but it'll do just fine.

Change-Id: I4d79a11e55adb1925b983732423ee5cb1dc54f1c
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>

Make use of the typing_extensions package, which contains backported
fixes from the stdlib typing package, to fix support for Python 3.7.

commit_message:
Add AMD Sev instance creation test

Test the ability to launch an AMD Sev guest instance [1]. Create the
necessary image/flavor to launch this type of guest. Confirm
memoryBacking and  launchSecurity are present in the guest XML:

  <memory unit='KiB'>65536</memory>
  <currentMemory unit='KiB'>65536</currentMemory>
  <memoryBacking>
    <locked/>
  </memoryBacking>
...
  <launchSecurity type='sev'>
    <cbitpos>47</cbitpos>
    <reducedPhysBits>1</reducedPhysBits>
    <policy>0x0033</policy>
  </launchSecurity>

Validate all devices with model type virtio also has iommu enabled for
the driver:

    <memballoon model='virtio'>
      <stats period='10'/>
      <alias name='balloon0'/>
      <address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x04' slot='0x00' function='0x0'/>
      <driver iommu='on'/>
    </memballoon>

Lastly confirm AMD Sev is active from within the guest.

Test leveraged methods in test_vgpu so those methods were migrated to
the base class.

commit_message:
WIP: adding user visible extra_spec for encryption

This patch adds an extra_spec "encryption_enabled" that is
automatically set and unset when creating or deleting
encryption types. It is not setable elsewhere.
Due to this new extra_spec non-Admin users can now see, whether
a volume type can create encrypted volumes or not.

Change-Id: Iba216a5f0d8af0f82f27275150b48755857448b1

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I02db2ad91ad036ff24c35882e1746b3d6a8f3cc0

commit_message:
CI: Remove grenade branch variables

This was always testing the upgrade with master, causing CI failures on
the stable/2024.1 branch.

Also remove USE_PYTHON3 which is always true in our supported branches.

Change-Id: I9ba2b02b7c5abd2b6a2114cd3b680ea0244484a4

commit_message:
Fix devstack runprocess for cloudkitty api

After the commit
https://github.com/openstack/pbr/commit/8778c64776b092065988d92865ebaf2892930493

The module PBR in openstack started to validating the parameters when
creating an embedded WSGI, now if invalid arguments are given
to the cloudkitty-api it raises an error as we are facing in the
devstack when using `CLOUDKITTY_USE_MOD_WSGI=False`:

cloudkitty-api[86126]: usage: cloudkitty-api [-h] [--port PORT] [--host IP] -- [passed options]
cloudkitty-api[86126]: cloudkitty-api: error: unrecognized arguments: --config-file=/etc/cloudkitty/cloudkitty.conf

This PR also extracts the upgrade database workflow to a function
to be used in grenade tests

Change-Id: Ifc1a8563a9efcae2abaa6f8eb036405a93ff296d
(cherry picked from commit 25a73064123236529c1abfc9a9feb81c58c96de5)

commit_message:
neutron: add service role

After Neutron policy changes - Octavia jobs started
to fail on cascade LB deletion due to Neutron user
not having service role.

Closes-Bug: #2065337

commit_message:
Optimize deletion of static routes

Instead of having a separate OVN command for deletion of each
static route, send out the deletion as a single command.

Which significantly improves the performance. Previously
deletion of 1000 routes took >1m30s and >6m30s for 2000 routes,
with this change it takes ~5s and ~8s, respectivily.

Closes-Bug: #2060054
Change-Id: Iaa5204e2e48795c31c502160041bd128189eef5a

commit_message:
Remove support for legacy store setup

This change removes the legacy store support which was deprecated in
favor of support for the multi-store setup[1].

[1] fd02761c6e634100ce4583c88a092f2958742ae7

Also, the deprecated filesystem_store_* parameters are removed because
these are used only when the legacy store is used and were deprecated
formally during the previous cycle[2].

[2] 0e6fd040e51dec569ff64078109de2248b49b0ed

Change-Id: Ia2100578725fcb7c2e35d09bd37f27e555b36879

commit_message:
Add rating modules PUT endpoint to v2 API

This introduces the PUT method for rating modules in the v2 API. Work items:

* Implement the "/v1/rating/modules" endpoints in the v2 API, including
  unit tests and documentation

Story: 2006572

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I6f1131cb9c8f15d7d9367397ff8ca1b439d66ab0

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Change-Id: Idd3bb9a0ab58307b6acced6dd60fce3adf17b138

commit_message:
Add service policies defenition

In order to allow definition of policies per service, we need to add variables
to service roles, that will be passed to openstack.osa.mq_setup.

Currently this can be handled by leveraging group_vars and overriding `oslomsg_rpc_policies` as a whole, but it's not obvious and
can be non-trivial for some groups which are co-locating multiple services
or in case of metal deployments.

Change-Id: If239bee6267b983cf335c37ce9fb26bd352a3921

commit_message:
Add qos_prefetch_count to variables

When rabbit_stream_fanout is set to true, rabbit_qos_prefetch_count
should be set to a positive value.

This also fixes defenition of transient_quorum_queue as if
rabbit_stream_fanout is enabled - transient_quorum_queue should be also
enabled. [1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/master/oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_rabbit.py#L726-L736

Change-Id: I8ea72890948ef1c4516c6272c3b19e81693e611a

commit_message:
Add service policies defenition

In order to allow definition of policies per service, we need to add variables
to service roles, that will be passed to openstack.osa.mq_setup.

Currently this can be handled by leveraging group_vars and overriding `oslomsg_rpc_policies` as a whole, but it's not obvious and
can be non-trivial for some groups which are co-locating multiple services
or in case of metal deployments.

Change-Id: I1258e2dc385d8d004091167835e9c14e314cbc2b
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-ansible-os_swift refs/changes/70/919070/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD

commit_message:
[OpenStackAnsible] Transition Zed to Unmaintained

This branch reached the end of its official stable maintained period,
hence this patch transition stable/zed branch to Unmaintained. (For
details about Unmaintained state please see: [1][2])

The transitions is as follows:
- tip of the stable/zed branch is tagged with zed-eom tag
- unmaintained/zed branch will be cut from zed-eom tag
- stable/zed branch will be deleted

Note:
- there will no longer be official releases off of zed branch after this
  transition
- backports can be pushed to unmaintained/yoga branch
- openstack-unmaintained-core (or <project>-unmaintained-core groups if
  such exists) have the rights to merge patches

Important: please +1 if the team is ready for us to proceed with this
transition, or -1 if there are any final Zed stable release with
backports currently in flight that we should wait for. For the latter
case, please propose a final Zed stable release patch, and rebase this
patch on top of that, with the latest commit hash of stable/zed.

The transition deadline is May 2nd, 2024. [3]

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/project-team-guide/stable-branches.html#unmaintained
[2] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/resolutions/20230724-unmaintained-branches.html
[3] https://releases.openstack.org

Change-Id: I7a7732fc7fe5b07ca1fa06dec2f45d676dff959f
